cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the design and optimization of a network architecture for IoT devices, which involves wireless communication and power transfer. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and optimization, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely category. The use of stochastic geometry for modeling the network indicates cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as the third likely category. The paper also discusses the integration of power and communication, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper mentions the potential applications of the proposed network in multimedia communication, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as the fifth likely category.
